list.name: 7fd30824-e20c-473e-b906-f4f30ebc4bb0
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Biotic charger that can travel to enemies in the blink of an eye, then deal point-blank damage.

The Human Vanguard is a talented Alliance veteran who hopes he can relive his glory days in Andromeda. He often gives advice to the younger members of the team and loves to say, "I told you so."

list.name: 32672912-52e6-43f0-a717-f850d1799c44
list.locDescription:
Uncommon Class: Explosives technician with high survivability and area damage.

This is great! Who knew all those science lessons she had to take would be so handy? If only she could brag to her friends back home about her cool new team and how much fun fighting these little kett guys is.

list.name: 5c968651-a686-458e-b100-355b5f378734
list.locDescription:
Ultra Rare Class: Biotic tank that pulls in targets and devastates them with point-blank, area-of-effect attacks.

The Krogan Gladiator's family thought she should be taking care of her kin instead of being a soldier. She lives to prove them wrong and show the world she is a force to be reckoned with.

list.name: 7caddce0-7869-47f3-b97c-2a2ae9018042
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Slow-moving tank with all the heavy weapons and armor a fighter could want. 

Can the Krogan Mercenary kill it? Will it be glorious? Excellent. He'll buy the first round of ryncol when the battle is over.

list.name: c93824de-3fc5-49c6-9893-1fff7a7de53f
list.locDescription:
Uncommon Class: Tough biotic warrior with point-blank damage who quickly travels to enemies. 

After getting drunk and missing his Rite of Passage on Tuchanka, the shame and disappointment drove the Krogan Vanguard to join up with the Initiative. He has a few anger management issues and likes to hit things. Hard.

list.name: 4245cc53-2c07-4dd2-9ee3-fbd20ead05cf
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Exchanges personal damage and defense for a deadly robot VI. 

The Salarian Architect's former colleagues at the lab he worked at are quietly relieved that he ended up in the Initiative. He's exceptionally smart, but quite quirky; he seems to get along better with his VI drones than with living creatures.

list.name: 0f33bfbf-207b-4028-a7df-e7e8a0b262a6
list.locDescription:
Uncommon Class: Stealth expert that uses a mix of weapons and tech. 

A former member of the Salarian Special Task Group, the Salarian Infiltrator found the organization's secrecy tiresome and dropped out to join the Initiative. He likes to make quiet entrances, but once the job's done, he's the first to start bragging.

list.name: 1a784297-8aa7-4668-8040-e785be835c7e
list.locDescription:
Ultra Rare Class: Support expert that repairs shields and hacks enemy hardsuit defenses.

Badgered into volunteering for the Initiative by his father, the Salarian Operator isn't quite sure why these APEX people think he can actually help them, and would really rather be working on tech at an outpost site. But if he's here, he'll try to make the best of it.

list.name: 07dc4ede-8120-4fa5-90e5-aefc5c0bcbf5
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Special agent that can sneak behind enemy lines using a versatile power set.

The Turian Agent left a dull corporate security job in the Milky Way to find adventure with the Andromeda Initiative. His professionalism and confidence can make him seem snobbish, but he genuinely cares about the team.

list.name: 324979c8-22cc-4217-8c44-8924c340023d
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Propulsion expert that specializes in aerial combat. 

The Turian Havoc Trooper is a bit more…boisterous than the average turian solder. She's very good at what she does, and enjoys it just a little too much to be cold and professional about it.

list.name: b2e2cd83-028b-4b51-b088-6fa3fe6146eb
list.locDescription:
Uncommon Class: Weapons expert with heavy shields and armor.

To avoid a court martial on Palaven for his role in a massacre, the Turian Soldier went on the lam and worked as a mercenary until he was able to buy his way into the Initiative.

list.name: 8aaa77b2-d04d-4d86-a629-4964530ff603
list.locDescription:
Ultra Rare Class: Close-combat escape artist with stealth ability for evades and melee attacks. 

The Angara Avenger lost her mother to the kett at a young age. Since then, she has vowed to bring every kett to justice and hopes to one day face off against the Archon himself.

list.name: 3b53a170-7228-4ea7-81e8-8a1baaca64e4
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Master of holding one location with traps and localized support. 

These kett invaders need to back off of the Angara Insurgent's territory. Seriously. These new aliens fighting with him might be useful, but someone needs to show them how things work in this galaxy.

list.name: c421b264-cddf-4170-9ca3-296a55a0ec49
list.locDescription:
Uncommon Class: A mighty biotic that compensates for light armor with crowd-control attacks and widespread damage. 

An Alliance veteran, the Asari Adept has seen combat before and looks out for the younger members of the team. She enjoys crowd control, and enjoys the sense of satisfaction when the team works well together.

list.name: 00deb555-5cb5-4473-ac9a-22e9d1ac2328
list.locDescription:
Ultra Rare Class: Biotic warrior with a sword, high mobility, and both damage and defense powers. 

The Asari Duelist is a former Justicar. She keeps her distance from the other team members and harbors doubts about whether she made the right choice in coming to a new galaxy.

list.name: 501b0540-e81f-4522-aa40-21e384347285
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Mobile fighter with biotic powers who can cloak allies. 

In the Milky Way, the Asari Huntress was a well-regarded bounty hunter until she took the wrong job and found herself on the most-wanted list. She joined the Andromeda Initiative to escape her enemies and begin the hunt anew.

list.name: 4f49ce2e-2d63-4011-90da-f5b61ccb58e5
list.locDescription:
Uncommon Class: Tactical defense expert with tech armor and a versatile power set. 

A former asari commando, the Asari Sentinel joined APEX to escape some of the... less-pleasant things she experienced while serving in her commando unit.

list.name: e2f76cf1-4b42-4dba-9751-f2add5c3f654
list.locDescription:
Common Class: A powerful biotic with light armor who uses powers to control crowds and cause widespread damage.

The Human Adept doesn't much care about the romance of settling a new galaxy. What she sees here is a power vacuum—and she's damn well going to fill it.

list.name: e4357633-93bc-4596-99c3-4cc0a49b2277
list.locDescription:
Common Class: A powerful biotic with light armor who uses powers to control crowds and cause widespread damage.

The Human Adept doesn't really talk about why he joined the Initiative; in fact, he doesn't talk much at all. Given the quiet intensity with which he rips through enemies, none of his teammates are rushing to ask about his past.

list.name: c756c741-1bc8-47a8-9f35-b7ca943ba034
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Clever tech expert that distracts, limits, and locks down opponents on the battlefield. 

Exuberant and enthusiastic, the Human Engineer loves using creative tech to blow things up. If it does the job and makes a spectacular explosion doing so, that's the best of both worlds.

list.name: a3960123-3625-4126-82e4-1f9a127d33aa
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Clever tech expert that distracts, limits, and locks down opponents on the battlefield. 

The Human Engineer was always good at science, but he knows he's got what it takes to be a leader—leaders should be the smart people, after all. He'll be a Pathfinder some day, just you wait and see.

list.name: cae8a2f3-fdaf-471c-9391-c29f6d4308c3
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Stealth expert who moves unnoticed around the battlefield with tech powers, then picks off enemies with well-placed shots. 

After losing her husband and child in a botched robbery back in the Milky Way, the Human Infiltrator came to Andromeda for a fresh start. She joined APEX to do some good—and to work through some anger and sadness.

list.name: 34aeef66-a030-445e-98e2-1513c0c78df4
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Stealth expert who moves unnoticed around the battlefield with tech powers, then picks off enemies with well-placed shots. 

One of the younger team members, the Human Infiltrator is more thrill-seeker than hardened combatant. His natural abilities make him effective, and his reckless nature can work both for and against him.

list.name: c328be40-7b88-4e72-9312-8c5987da5541
list.locDescription:
Ultra Rare Class: A biotic warrior that deals serious damage with telekinesis and the ability to enter a powered-up state, but has weak defenses.

A scientist through-and-through, the Human Kineticist can't wait to test her theories in real-life settings and gets a bit annoyed if something disrupts her experiments. Yes, fine, take down enemies—but the science!

list.name: 319ffe5d-f8fb-4217-bd2f-2e8af4f53fc8
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Tactical defense expert with sturdy tech armor and a versatile power set. 

Excited to seek adventure, this is the Human Sentinel's first time testing her combat skills in a real-life situation. She's very skilled, and what she lacks in experience, she makes up for in enthusiasm.

list.name: baae0381-8690-4097-ae6d-0c16473519b4
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Tactical defense expert with sturdy tech armor and a versatile power set.

The Human Sentinel is a seasoned professional; he's been there and done that. Nothing surprises him, even in a brand-new galaxy.

list.name: 79f3511c-55da-67f0-5002-359c370015d8
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Weapons expert with heavy armor and a gun for all occasions. Effective at any range.

The Human Soldier worked private security in the Terminus System, but left to find adventure in Andromeda. She likes getting to know her new APEX colleagues and working with them to get the job done well.

list.name: af3a2cf0-dff7-4ca8-9199-73ce546c3e7b
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Weapons expert with heavy armor and a gun for all occasions. Effective at any range.

The Human Soldier worked in the Alliance before joining the Initiative. He likes the idea of helping establish life in a new world, and he wants to do it in the way he thinks is noble and right.

list.name: 96fa16c5-9f2b-46f8-a491-a4b0a24a1089
list.locDescription:
Common Class: Biotic charger that can travel to enemies in the blink of an eye, then deal point-blank damage. 

The Human Female Vanguard was a respected leader within the Alliance, so Initiative leaders recruited her to organize and establish security organizations in Andromeda. APEX is more than the "segue to eventual retirement" she'd anticipated, but she's good at her job and respected by the team.

list.locDescription:
Ultra Rare Class: Angaran Resistance fighter with bioelectric abilities, ranged damage, and combo detonations. 

The Angara Exemplar has years of combat training and doesn't have much patience with these new aliens and their unconventional ways. Still, the newcomers are feet on the ground, so he'll put up with them for the greater good.

list.name: c1dc3878-3761-4278-881c-d3fe9ee8d87a
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Brawler tank who locks down enemies and devastates them at melee range.

The Scrapper is one of two batarians who provided evidence against the leader of their former pirate gang. When Alliance protection services failed, the batarians negotiated an asylum deal with the Initiative.

The salarians granted the batarians cryo pods on Ark Paarchero to gain potential security assets. Happy to abandon pirate life, the Scrapper is starting to enjoy fighting for a greater purpose.

list.locDescription: Outlaws cobbled together the compact Shorty because they wanted a close-range weapon with extra ammo. The shotgun fires three-round bursts, but is heavy to carry because of a large ammunition clip; the recoil kicks like an angry mule.

list.name: f6e86182-7fbf-4f47-a99c-0ed795dd7f4e
list.locDescription:
Ultra Rare Class: Batarian Vanguard who uses biotics to close in on his opponents and pummel them with devastating melee attacks.

The Vanguard is one of two batarians given asylum on the salarian ark in exchange for helping the Alliance capture their former boss, who led a notorious batarian pirate gang that attacked ships uncomfortably close to the Citadel.

The two batarians were granted passage on the salarian ark in exchange for information and an agreement to provide security for future salarian settlements in Andromeda.

list.name: 088efa63-ebdf-4fe5-a52c-0eefa0c92852
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: A close-quarters tank with ramping offense and defense.

The biotic Juggernaut sharpened his skills on Omega in staged fights and scattered jobs as a hit man. The Juggernaut has burned every bridge he's ever built, but is still a team player—a larger team just means more kills for everyone. When APEX needed a soldier to test their experimental Remnant armor, the Juggernaut volunteered.

list.name: a70b7b8b-62b5-4f92-ba6f-68794a1ed2d0
list.locDescription: The Silhesh, translated to "disorder," is a smaller version of the Thokin assault rifle used by kett fighters in the field. Like the Thokin, the Silhesh SMG allows the kett to shoot tracking-enabled, plasma-surrounded rounds with a lightning-quick rate of fire.

list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Construct specialist who debuffs enemy troops.

Back in the Milky Way, the Artificer was a high school computer science teacher; her students loved her, but knew not to cross her. In the evenings, she trained students at the same kenpo dojo where she received her 4th-degree black belt. She's the embodiment of tough love. Nothing fazes her. Not even aliens with guns.

list.name: 3b4b3141-e77c-49e6-a658-f85e8b0518b1
list.locDescription: A semi-automatic assault rifle, the Sovoa fires energy blasts that cause a shockwave-like explosion upon impact. The elegance of the single-beam blast matches the rifle's sleek design. The Sovoa, translated to "lights out," is the first weapon developed by Taravay Industries, a new manufacturer co-founded by angara and turians. A product of two galaxies, the rifle combines Milky Way kinetic coils with angaran explosives.

list.name: 177f7a0f-831c-4c20-8768-252617eb5a0d
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Biotic soldier specializing in offensive crowd control.

The Commando served the Alliance as an elite offensive specialist for years until the Andromeda Initiative's recruitment efforts presented her with the opportunity to travel farther than she ever dreamed. She convinced the Guardian, a fellow soldier and her secret love, to accompany her. Now in Heleus, they fight side by side to create a new home for humanity.

list.name: 6cc6eaab-2290-4e9c-bb57-0f8c17136157
list.locDescription:
Rare Class: Biotic/Sentinel tank, specializing in defending and restoring his comrades.

The Guardian was an elite Alliance solder, deployed when a dangerous situation required the best and brightest. A master of defensive tactics, he became popular among his squadmates. Over the years, he and the Commando became close, although duty required they keep their personal relationship hidden from their comrades. The Andromeda Initiative struck them as a perfect way to serve while living as partners—on and off the field.
